The paper discusses distributed computing and decision-making in various models, which are all subfields of computer science. The most relevant sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which specifically deals with distributed computing. The paper also discusses algorithms and data structures for decision-making, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The models considered in the paper, such as LOCAL, CONGEST, WAIT-FREE, and FSYNC, are all related to distributed systems and synchronization, which are subfields of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also falls under the cs.Distributed sub-category, which covers various aspects of distributed computing. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning), as some of the decision-making algorithms discussed in the paper may be related to machine learning techniques.
